# Code Review Agent - Cursor Rules
# This configures Cursor AI to assist with this codebase effectively

## Project Context
This is an AI-powered code review agent built with Python and the Anthropic Claude API.
It specializes in detecting security vulnerabilities, performance issues, logic bugs, and style problems.

## Core Rules

### Code Style
- Use Python type hints on all function signatures
- Write docstrings for every function (Google style)
- Keep functions under 50 lines; extract helpers when needed
- Use f-strings for string formatting
- Prefer pathlib.Path over os.path

### Architecture Principles
- Agent logic lives in agent/reviewer.py
- Batch processing lives in agent/batch_review.py
- All API calls go through the `client` singleton in reviewer.py
- Never hardcode API keys — always use os.environ
- Structured JSON output from Claude, always validated before returning

### When Adding Features
- New review categories (e.g., accessibility, test coverage) → add to SYSTEM_PROMPT categories
- New output formats → add to format_report() or create new formatter
- New language support → extend ext_map in review_file()
- Performance improvements → look at batch_review.py max_workers

### Testing
- All test files go in tests/
- Use pytest
- Mock Anthropic API calls in tests — never make real API calls in tests
- Run: pytest tests/ -v

### Security
- NEVER commit .env files
- NEVER log full code content
- NEVER print API keys or tokens
- Always sanitize file paths before reading

### Common Patterns in This Codebase

# Calling the review agent:
from agent.reviewer import review_file, review_code
result = review_file("path/to/code.py")
result = review_code(code_string, language="python", context="Django view")

# The result is always a dict with keys:
# summary, score, issues, strengths, metrics

### Anthropic API Usage
- Model: claude-opus-4-5
- Max tokens: 2048 for reviews
- Always parse JSON from response.content[0].text
- Strip markdown fences before JSON.loads()

### DO NOT
- Do not use async/await (keep sync for simplicity)
- Do not store review history to disk without user consent
- Do not send full file contents larger than 100KB to the API
- Do not modify the JSON schema returned by the agent without updating format_report()
